<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>They focus on quantity instead of timing.</strong> More plantings do not help if they are poorly spaced.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They rely on guesswork.</strong> Without clear maturity data, succession planting becomes inconsistent.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They ignore late-season constraints.</strong> The final plantings are often the hardest to complete successfully.
  </p>
</section>

